{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_2","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' __issue_context__.json\"","aggregated_output":"{\n  \"body\": \"https://enzyme.expasy.org/EC/1.13.11.37\\r\\nEntry: EC:1.13.11.37\\r\\nAccepted Name: hydroxyquinol 1,2-dioxygenase\\r\\nReaction catalysed: benzene-1,2,4-triol + O2 <=> 2 H(+) + maleylacetate\\r\\n\\r\\nThat EC is currently on two GO terms (shown below), it's an exact match for the second one (GO:0047074) that describes the 'complete 2-step reaction', but should only be a 'broadMatch' for the first one (GO:0018581) that only describes the first step of the reaction. (The second step in non-enzymatic conversion of 3-hydroxy-cis,cis-muconate to maleylacetate - see https://biocyc.org/META/NEW-IMAGE?type=REACTION&object=RXN-10137)\\r\\nTasks:\\r\\n- [x] Make EC:1.13.11.37 xref on GO:0018581 a 'broadMatch'\\r\\n- [x] Remove EC:1.13.11.37-attributed synonyms from GO:0018581 (EC:1.13.11.37 currently doesn't list any synonyms)\\r\\n- [x] Change GO:0018581 def attribution to use RHEA:19441\\r\\n- [x] Make EC:1.13.11.37 xref on GO:0047074 a 'exactMatch'\\r\\n- [x] Tweak GO:0047074 def to match EC:1.13.11.37 def\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nid: GO:0018581\\r\\nname: hydroxyquinol 1,2-dioxygenase activity\\r\\ndef: \\\"Catalysis of the reaction: benzene-1,2,4-triol + O2 = 3-hydroxy-cis,cis-muconate.\\\" [EC:1.13.11.37]\\r\\nsynonym: \\\"benzene-1,2,4-triol:oxygen 1,2-oxidoreductase (decyclizing)\\\" RELATED [EC:1.13.11.37]\\r\\nsynonym: \\\"hydroxyquinol dioxygenase activity\\\" RELATED [EC:1.13.11.37]\\r\\nxref: EC:1.13.11.37\\r\\nxref: MetaCyc:HYDROXYQUINOL-12-DIOXYGENASE-RXN\\r\\nxref: RHEA:19441\\r\\nxref: UM-BBD_reactionID:r0232\\r\\nis_a: GO:0016702 ! oxidoreductase activity, acting on single donors with incorporation of molecular oxygen, incorporation of two atoms of oxygen\\r\\n\\r\\nid: GO:0047074\\r\\nname: 4-hydroxycatechol 1,2-dioxygenase activity\\r\\nnamespace: molecular_function\\r\\ndef: \\\"Catalysis of the reaction: O2 + benzene-1,2,4-triol = maleylacetate.\\\" [RHEA:35595]\\r\\nxref: EC:1.13.11.37\\r\\nxref: MetaCyc:R308-RXN\\r\\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-10137\\r\\nxref: RHEA:35595\\r\\nis_a: GO:0016702 ! oxidoreductase activity, acting on single donors with incorporation of molecular oxygen, incorporation of two atoms of oxygen\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\",\n  \"comments\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws5jRjOX\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"sjm41\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"Also:\\r\\n\\r\\n- [x] MetaCyc:HYDROXYQUINOL-12-DIOXYGENASE-RXN is obsolete. Replace with RXN-17556.\\r\\n- [x] MetaCyc:R308-RXN is obsolete. Remove.\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2023-08-04T12:40:37Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": true,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25870#issuecomment-1665545111\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABAQaW9Q\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"sjm41\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"Looking at this one again, we should:\\n- [x] Obsolete GO:0018581, because it's a sub-reaction of RHEA:35595 (it has 0 GO annotations anyway)\\n- [x] Then rename GO:0047074 to \\\"hydroxyquinol 1,2-dioxygenase activity\\\" (the name currently on GO:0018581), since that's the EC name.\\n\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-24T09:43:43Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": true,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [\n        {\n          \"content\": \"THUMBS_UP\",\n          \"users\": {\n            \"totalCount\": 1\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25870#issuecomment-4312176373\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABApx